The paper deals with image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a genetic algorithm for optimization suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Simulated Binary Crossover (SBX) as a recombination operator is a technique commonly used in optimization problems in the continuous domain, which suggests a possible fit with graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the use of a noisy fitness evaluation is a technique commonly used in evolutionary algorithms, which suggests a possible fit with neural networks (cs.NE).
